		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=89825"><span id=Sage>Colphax Quick Hands</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />195 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Colphax&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Sorry Bladedsong, but your idea about rangers in EQ has some big problems with EQ realities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unfortunately, archery as a primary form of combat is only possible from 55 on.  At 55, a ranger can use Trueshot discipline every hour or so, but that's simply not enough to go full archery while your waiting for your disc timer to count down.  For one thing, you are most definately going to run out of arrows (even if you have a Tolan's bracer, that thing takes time to cast).  The only time that archery can outdamage melee is when the ranger has BOTH Endless Quiver and Archery Mastery 3, the best arrows, and a truly nice bow.  in order to get all that, unfortunately, means you are going to have to melee your butt off for a long time, since all this can only happen when you are at least level 59.<br /><br />Sad fact of the matter is that Sony/Verant threw in archery as an afterthought...it was never supposed to be a primary form of combat when the game was fist created.  This explains why so many rangers see a string of utterly disgusting archery hits of 1's and 4's so often in their careers up until they get Archery Mastery.<br /><br />Let's say you are bound and determined to prove me wrong, however, and that you will make an archery-only ranger from day one.  You are gonna be so broke it's not funny.  In order to get decent damage, you are going to need to make LOTS and LOTS of the absolute best arrows you can.  Then you are going to have to carry all those components with you everywhere you go, since you will burn through an entire quiver (more likely more) of arrows for each kill.  Don't mention a mage bot...you are still going to need far more arrows than you think!<br /><br />Not to mention, you are going to need the best bow you can find...the lower delay the better.  That's gonna be more expensive to buy and shoot.   Let's not talk about the level restrictions the nice stat-raising bows that arte even more expensive have.<br /><br />Also, if you are going to go full archery, you are going to need a lot of dex gear...problem is your DEX focused ranger is gonna have a hard time hauling all this junk AND a set of armor and supplies!<br /><br />And what about spells!!!  How will this archery-only ranger afford his new spells if all his money is going to arrows?<br /><br />Sorry, Bladedsong, but your ranger will do far far more damage in melee over archery for a long time.  All that you need to do is learn how to use a rangers strengths while minimizing the weaknesses.  If you play a ranger in melee like a warrior, you are gonna die..a lot...gruesomely...again and again...</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >2 Replies</td></tr></table>
