		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Taskiss&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I'm sorry, I do not agree with your assesment of the ranger archery skill. Yes, it would be wonderful if all my shots were the 202 max that I just recently got. however, in solo hunting, I've found that using the stinging swarm, immolate and my bow were quite sufficient to bring down a elder shardwurm (dark blue to my lvl 52 ranger). I could not have done that using melee techniques. Yes, in a group, my damage with 1hs and 2hs far outweighs the damage possible... but only in damage per second. moving fast and failing to kill the mob isn't going to do it. and your understanding of arrows seems to be off a bit, too. I've made class 6 arrows and class 3 arrows and compared (by how many I shot in killing giants at raithe) and don't see much difference, so I shoot only class 3 arrows now. so, more expensive isn't better, the way you seemed to suggest. (edited for spelling errors)<br /><br /><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb 26 14:34:17 2003</em></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
