 a ranger as rangers were meant to be.<br /><br />Just that all the lords of heaven and hell that you didn't decide to be a paladin.<br /><br />And then, after you gain a few levels and accumulate a lot of cash from the LARGE amounts of things that you kite without fear of dying in melee, get all your spells, etc, you can think about blacksmithing for your arrowheads and other things.<br /><br />And the fact that rangers are hybrids and can cast makes the fact that there's downtime not important. After all, downtime is something that happens, plain and simple. No matter what, you cannot get through a battle without downtime (unless you're killing stuff like decaying skellies)</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=643308" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=643308</a><br /><br />Oh yeah. See the master enchanter. Uber level 12. (If you can't tell that I'm being sarcastic...)<br /><br />Darkfire Soldiers all the way!</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
